w open source and community awareness for HashiCorp security solutions. Sustainably grow commercial revenue Perform and mentor product managers to conduct market analysis including evaluations and decisions for whether to expand into new markets and products. Craft the product story by understanding the landscape, user needs, and HashiCorp principles. Engage with key customers and community members to drive roadmaps. Review and approve the roadmaps submitted by product managers. Mentor product managers and give feedback on their work \u2014 user research, Product Requirement Documents (PRDs), field engagement, roadmaps. Partner with the marketing, design and engineering teams to deliver on roadmap. Communicate product status to all partners. Keep sales and marketing updated on feature releases and keep engineering informed on feature requests. Orchestrate technical sales training for pre-sales engineers. Help with sales and marketing collateral to educate on the product story and features (Website copy, whitepapers, sales decks, FAQs, etc). You may be a good fit for our team if you have: Experience leading product portfolios with $100m+ annual revenue 5+ years of product management experience with security products 5+ years managing other product managers Strong user and market research skills Ability to organize multiple stakeholders towards a common goal Strong technical acumen, with a solid understanding of the security market Experience with managing open source products preferred but not required Experience with SaaS products preferred but not required Experience with deep product design collaboration preferred but not required Attributes we look for in successful product managers: Humility and learning mindset Information seeking Explain complex ideas simply Written, verbal, and visual communication skills Responsible and takes ownership over work HashiCorp embraces diversity and equal opportunity. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety 